{"key":"post-16115364","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>16115364</id>\n<content>When you can touch a jar to the most sensitive parts of your arm such as the inside of the wrist and it's lukewarm or cooler, it's safe to inoculate.&amp;nbsp; It usually works out best to sterilize in the evening and inoculate the next morning.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;small&quot;&gt;Quote:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Although the jars might have seemed cool on the outside inside it was still too hot. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;post&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;small&quot;&gt;Quote:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;And that means the inside is alot hotter than the surface of the jar.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;post&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/lol.gif&quot; alt=&quot;:lol:&quot; title=&quot;:lol:&quot;/&gt; This always cracks me the hell up, but it keeps gets repeated as if it were true.&amp;nbsp; When was the last time anyone picked up a cold cup of coffee, only to scald their lips taking a drink?&amp;nbsp; A BRF cake is moist, and water is an excellent heat conductor.&amp;nbsp; There will be no more than a few degrees of difference between the center of the jar and the glass as it cools.&amp;nbsp; If the glass is cool, the contents are too and safe to inoculate.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>16115323</prev>\n<first>16114520</first>\n<last>16115364</last>\n<when>1334930515</when>\n<utime>04/20/12 05:01 PM</utime>\n</post>"}